WEBVTT



00:00:00.864 --> 00:00:04.576
Friends, welcome to Word on Fire Catholic Ministries.

00:00:04.384 --> 00:00:09.824
Word on Fire is an apostolate dedicated to the mission of evangelization.

00:00:09.600 --> 00:00:15.008
Using media both old and new to share the faith on every continent,

00:00:14.784 --> 00:00:18.752
and to facilitate an encounter with Christ and His Church.

00:00:18.848 --> 00:00:27.008
The efforts of Word on Fire engage the culture and bring the transformative power of God's Word where it is most needed.

00:00:27.040 --> 00:00:36.448
Today, we invite you to join Bishop Robert Barron as he preaches the Gospel and shares the warmth and light of Christ with each one of us.

00:00:39.552 --> 00:00:44.928
Peace be with you. Friends, this year has been kind of unusual because Easter was a bit late.

00:00:44.512 --> 00:00:46.752
Yeah. And then, you know, we go through.

00:00:47.104 --> 00:00:57.152
And then we come to Feast of Holy Trinity and then Corpus Christi, and then we have the Feast of Peter and Paul. So all this is delayed the beginning.

00:00:56.672 --> 00:01:01.600
Guinea or the resumption of ordinary time. So finally now on July the 6th, 2024, the U.S.

00:01:01.184 --> 00:01:06.176
Yeah. We resume ordinary time. And it's appropriate, I think, that...

00:01:05.952 --> 00:01:11.136
We're looking at a portrait of the church as we do so, because we're coming back if you want to the

00:01:10.880 --> 00:01:13.504
ordinary work of the Church.

00:01:13.504 --> 00:01:20.480
up and down the ages to the present day. So I'm going to go through this passage from the 10th chapter of Luke and just look at it in terms of

00:01:20.768 --> 00:01:24.256
of providing a template for the life of the church.

00:01:24.160 --> 00:01:25.664
So listen first.

00:01:26.016 --> 00:01:29.184
1. The Lord appointed a further 72. 1.

00:01:29.216 --> 00:01:34.272
And sent them in pairs before him to every town and place he intended to visit.

00:01:34.592 --> 00:01:36.288
Here's the first thing we have to see.

00:01:37.088 --> 00:01:40.672
Inescapably, the church is missionary.

00:01:40.736 --> 00:01:42.880
Jesus took these people and

00:01:42.944 --> 00:01:49.248
He didn't just instruct them and then say, "Now revel in the spiritual teaching I've given you."

00:01:49.280 --> 00:01:52.512
He always sends them.

00:01:52.576 --> 00:01:53.760
on mission.

00:01:54.016 --> 00:01:58.816
Mission just comes from the word, you know, "Mitere" Latin means "to send."

00:01:58.912 --> 00:02:03.040
An apostle, that's from a Greek word, apostelain, that means to send.

00:02:03.232 --> 00:02:05.792
Sending is essential to Christianity.

00:02:05.856 --> 00:02:13.280
So the last thing we're called upon to do is just, you know, okay, this is really benefiting me spiritually and now I'm done. I'm happy. Yeah.

00:02:13.888 --> 00:02:16.896
What you've received as a gift, give as a gift.

00:02:17.088 --> 00:02:20.800
I wonder up the state of bluntly, I wonder.

00:02:20.704 --> 00:02:26.080
How many Catholics really buy this? They really understand it. How many know Catholics?

00:02:25.792 --> 00:02:27.872
Their ultimate purpose is to

00:02:27.872 --> 00:02:30.240
To go forth from mass.

00:02:30.592 --> 00:02:36.224
Right. As indeed we say, right? Go, go, the Mass Sunday. Now go, crucify the world. Right.

00:02:36.608 --> 00:02:40.960
Every time you leave Mass, you've been sent into Mission Country.

00:02:40.832 --> 00:02:42.944
On mission territory.

00:02:43.104 --> 00:02:48.288
I don't know. I think we tend to internalize it all and privatize it.

00:02:48.480 --> 00:02:50.176
That's not Christianity.

00:02:50.592 --> 00:02:52.352
The gospel is like

00:02:52.160 --> 00:02:56.864
A seed that's meant to be sown. It's like a light that's meant to shine, right?

00:02:57.376 --> 00:02:59.552
And he sends them beautifully,

00:02:59.584 --> 00:03:00.800
Two by two.

00:03:01.376 --> 00:03:04.064
Look, we're in this together.

00:03:03.840 --> 00:03:13.888
Yeah. Mission work is never just solitary work. In fact, I think that's always a sign of something corrupt, something bad, something a bit dangerous.

00:03:13.408 --> 00:03:19.104
If you start saying, well, I figured it out. Here's my mission. I'm going to go do it.

00:03:19.520 --> 00:03:21.792
No, no, no. The Lord sends us...

00:03:21.824 --> 00:03:29.088
2x2 or 3x3 here, 1,000 by 1,000. He sends us always in community. You know, why? Why?

00:03:28.992 --> 00:03:34.656
Well, I mean, for a mutual support, that's one thing. It's awfully hard to do something totally on your own. Yeah.

00:03:34.464 --> 00:03:36.832
Also mutual correction.

00:03:36.672 --> 00:03:46.720
If you have more people around you while you're doing your work, you're less likely to be saying and doing something stupid. It's good to have people around you to correct you. We're in...

00:03:46.240 --> 00:03:47.424
And in this passage,

00:03:47.680 --> 00:03:48.864
Together.

00:03:48.928 --> 00:03:55.232
And to me, that's a very Catholic sensibility, too, is that it's never a lone wolf sort of enterprise.

00:03:55.104 --> 00:03:57.920
We are doing this now as a body.

00:03:57.696 --> 00:04:01.440
Think of so many of the saints. I'm always struck by this.

00:04:01.920 --> 00:04:04.224
A saint might begin...

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:14.048
with a very personal individual experience. Think of a Francis hearing the voice from the cross. You know, Francis rebuild my church. Think of Mother Teresa.

00:04:13.568 --> 00:04:21.376
Oh, the Teresa hearing on the train ride to Darjeeling, the voice of the Lord, are you willing to serve me in the poorest of the poor? Yes.

00:04:22.144 --> 00:04:26.208
But see, those two sayings in particular, but all the great sayings.

00:04:26.176 --> 00:04:28.896
As soon as they commence their work,

00:04:28.640 --> 00:04:30.912
They were joined by people.

00:04:31.072 --> 00:04:40.608
Invariably, they were joined by people. They came, like, sometimes in great numbers. Francis had thousands before he knew it following him.

00:04:40.352 --> 00:04:43.392
Mother Teresa, a lot of her former students came.

00:04:43.296 --> 00:04:51.968
Think of Rose Hawthorne, one of my favorite American saints, beginning simply caring for cancer patients and before she knew it.

00:04:51.776 --> 00:04:53.824
People were coming to join her.

00:04:53.728 --> 00:04:56.416
So we're sent, yes, indeed.

00:04:56.832 --> 00:04:59.424
2x2 were sent in company.

00:05:00.064 --> 00:05:01.536
Next, we hear...

00:05:01.760 --> 00:05:05.728
The harvest is rich, but the workers are few. Therefore, the

00:05:05.632 --> 00:05:08.512
Ask the harvest masters send

00:05:08.224 --> 00:05:10.080
workers to his harvest.

00:05:10.880 --> 00:05:12.832
Prayer, everybody.

00:05:13.024 --> 00:05:20.416
is not decorative, it's not incidental to the life of the church. It is the life blood of the church.

00:05:21.536 --> 00:05:27.040
I mean, if you don't ask the Lord for his help to send people, it's not going to happen. Right.

00:05:27.328 --> 00:05:32.960
You can be full of goodwill and full of projects and programs and boy, I'm going to do this, I'm going to do that.

00:05:32.640 --> 00:05:35.392
But if you're not asking the Lord,

00:05:35.552 --> 00:05:39.616
to support you. It's not going to happen.

00:05:39.808 --> 00:05:49.856
I've often said in the Bible, nothing great is ever accomplished apart from prayer. I don't know any great saint who ever did anything worthwhile that

00:05:49.376 --> 00:05:57.152
that wasn't accompanied by prayer. Go back to the Bible when King David or even young David before he's king,

00:05:56.896 --> 00:05:58.944
When he asks God,

00:05:58.848 --> 00:06:06.176
What should I do? He always finds the right path. When David goes bad, it's because he stops asking God.

00:06:06.816 --> 00:06:11.104
And so the church prays and prays and prays.

00:06:10.880 --> 00:06:13.504
There's contemplative prayer, sure, but

00:06:13.248 --> 00:06:16.864
But I think at the heart of the matter is petitionary prayer.

00:06:16.896 --> 00:06:22.176
"'We beg, we beg, we ask. "'Lord, guide me, Lord, send me, "'Lord, help me.'"

00:06:22.688 --> 00:06:24.096
Without that,

00:06:23.904 --> 00:06:26.112
Our work is in vain.

00:06:26.080 --> 00:06:36.128
And again, I think we miss out on this. And we give into a kind of maybe it's very modern, maybe even very American sense of self-reliance. And I got my program.

00:06:35.648 --> 00:06:37.760
program, and I'm going to figure it out.

00:06:38.944 --> 00:06:44.384
Ipso facto you will fail in the measure that you're not praying.

00:06:45.184 --> 00:06:46.592
Well, then the Lord says,

00:06:46.816 --> 00:06:52.544
"'Do not carry a walking staff or traveling bag. "'Wear no sandals. "'Greet no one along the way.'"

00:06:53.120 --> 00:06:57.440
You know, translate walking staff, traveling bag.

00:06:57.888 --> 00:07:07.936
You mentioned coming to the airport, you're going to go on a trip and you have absolutely no luggage whatsoever and you have no wallet, you have no money, no credit.

00:07:07.456 --> 00:07:10.208
No credit cards and you have no luggage. Yeah.

00:07:10.464 --> 00:07:13.472
What kind of trips that going to be? Well, it'll be a 10

00:07:13.184 --> 00:07:16.800
A strange one, probably a very short one. But the point is, the point is,

00:07:17.376 --> 00:07:19.360
Do you do this work

00:07:19.296 --> 00:07:21.792
Relying upon yourself

00:07:21.792 --> 00:07:23.552
or relying upon God.

00:07:24.128 --> 00:07:33.280
This is why in so many of the spiritual traditions within Christianity, within so many of the religious orders, there's some moment such as this:

00:07:33.248 --> 00:07:37.216
When the young adept is asked to surrender

00:07:37.760 --> 00:07:44.384
It's a providence to let go of the things that have kept them safe. Right.

00:07:44.608 --> 00:07:45.760
Let go.

00:07:45.888 --> 00:07:48.192
And trust in God.

00:07:48.896 --> 00:07:51.072
Why so many of the great saints?

00:07:50.880 --> 00:07:57.728
are marked by poverty. Not because there's some kind of love for poverty in itself.

00:07:57.440 --> 00:08:00.128
But there's something about letting go.

00:08:00.128 --> 00:08:03.168
Of all the visible means of support,

00:08:04.128 --> 00:08:09.344
That permits you to rely on the invisible means of support, if that makes sense.

00:08:09.856 --> 00:08:17.440
It's easy enough when I got all these things around me. I got money and I got support and I got friends and I got institutional help.

00:08:17.632 --> 00:08:22.304
Well, okay, then off I go, but I'm relying on all these worldly things, right?

00:08:22.656 --> 00:08:25.152
But if I kick all that away,

00:08:25.728 --> 00:08:30.048
And I'm just trusting in God. So I'm praying, yes, but then...

00:08:29.888 --> 00:08:35.424
You know, that prayer gets so internalized that I can now trust in God and

00:08:36.128 --> 00:08:37.632
To take care of it.

00:08:38.144 --> 00:08:48.192
I think it's a mark of all the great missionary movements, all the great orders in the life of the church. There's this kind of letting go and cleaning out,

00:08:47.712 --> 00:08:48.864
moment

00:08:48.992 --> 00:08:52.832
Francis Clare, Dominic Ignatius, Mother Teresa, on and on.

00:08:52.736 --> 00:08:54.496
You'll find this dimension.

00:08:56.128 --> 00:09:00.992
Then notice this as maybe kind of a balancing principle.

00:09:01.408 --> 00:09:02.560
He says,

00:09:02.400 --> 00:09:05.792
10. Stay in the one house eating and drinking what they have and 11.

00:09:05.632 --> 00:09:08.832
For the laborer is worth his wage.

00:09:08.640 --> 00:09:15.424
Now, I've been talking a lot about, you know, those who go out and do the work and those who proclaim and those who are serving the poor and so on. Yeah.

00:09:15.840 --> 00:09:19.360
But a big part of the life of the church, everybody, is

00:09:19.136 --> 00:09:21.888
Those people who support the

00:09:21.760 --> 00:09:26.208
That work of the church who make it possible by their generosity

00:09:26.048 --> 00:09:27.264
Again, again.

00:09:27.232 --> 00:09:29.824
The labor is worth his wage.

00:09:29.888 --> 00:09:39.712
Well, who are these people in whose house these ministers are staying? See them as an anticipation of all those people up and down the ages to the present day.

00:09:39.360 --> 00:09:42.144
who support the work of the church.

00:09:42.112 --> 00:09:43.712
By their generosity.

00:09:44.064 --> 00:09:50.528
You know, I've come to know this well since I've been a church administrator these past many years, rector of

00:09:50.272 --> 00:09:55.328
I'm on the line, Seminary, Auxiliary, Bishop in L.A., now Bishop in Minnesota. Thank you.

00:09:55.136 --> 00:09:56.160
Um,

00:09:56.480 --> 00:10:00.800
We can't do our work apart from generous donors, period.

00:10:00.992 --> 00:10:11.040
Period. I mean, yes, we rely on collections on Sunday and so on, and that's, of course, a form of generosity. But we're not for people who say, I'm going to get...

00:10:10.560 --> 00:10:13.728
going to give a lot of my wealth to the work of the church, right?

00:10:13.952 --> 00:10:20.896
We wouldn't have schools. We wouldn't have hospitals. We would not have seminaries. We wouldn't have parish buildings.

00:10:21.440 --> 00:10:28.544
So it's a beautiful evocation here of all those people who, through their generosity, make the work of the church

00:10:28.480 --> 00:10:29.632
Possible.

00:10:30.208 --> 00:10:36.704
Yeah. I'll be kind of blunt. We're not that great at it, to be honest. If you look at –

00:10:36.896 --> 00:10:40.544
100% American Catholics. We're not that great. Right.

00:10:40.384 --> 00:10:42.848
And expressing our generosity.

00:10:43.360 --> 00:10:46.752
That's an essential part of the church for those who have means

00:10:47.136 --> 00:10:49.568
Give give give

00:10:49.984 --> 00:10:53.984
And then watch what the church does. He gets more specific. He says,

00:10:54.208 --> 00:10:56.000
Cure the sick there.

00:10:56.832 --> 00:10:59.296
I can't I think we underplay this

00:10:59.360 --> 00:11:05.120
The church's teacher, yeah, we get that. Churches celebrate the liturgy and prayer. Okay.

00:11:05.728 --> 00:11:07.520
But the first thing he says is,

00:11:07.424 --> 00:11:09.056
In terms of ministry,

00:11:08.832 --> 00:11:10.400
Sure, the sick there.

00:11:11.200 --> 00:11:17.120
The church is a source of salvation from solos in Latin, meaning health,

00:11:17.088 --> 00:11:20.480
That means health of the soul and mind, sure.

00:11:20.608 --> 00:11:23.744
But let's face it, it also means health of the body.

00:11:23.488 --> 00:11:26.816
Jesus spent a lot of time healing sick

00:11:26.848 --> 00:11:28.832
And broken bodies.

00:11:29.344 --> 00:11:32.032
Is that part of the church's work? Yeah.

00:11:32.160 --> 00:11:33.536
In fact, we have a...

00:11:33.280 --> 00:11:35.904
"'Sacrament,' called the anointing of the sick.'

00:11:36.224 --> 00:11:40.448
And not just praying for the sick. It is that. It's praying that they might be cured. Right.

00:11:40.928 --> 00:11:44.672
The church has hospitals indeed because of this command.

00:11:44.800 --> 00:11:51.680
And so maybe it's God healing through the secondary causality of nurses and doctors and technicians.

00:11:51.392 --> 00:11:53.280
don't overlook the fact

00:11:53.600 --> 00:11:56.768
A big part of the church's life is to heal.

00:11:57.728 --> 00:12:00.928
What are people sick and suffering around you? Well, I'm

00:12:00.800 --> 00:12:04.512
If you're part of the church, you're called upon to address them.

00:12:06.016 --> 00:12:08.544
And in the second grade task of the church, he says, he says,

00:12:08.992 --> 00:12:10.272
Proclaim

00:12:10.080 --> 00:12:12.160
that the reign of God is at hand.

00:12:12.416 --> 00:12:15.104
All right, the church cures the sick and...

00:12:14.976 --> 00:12:17.792
it proclaims the kingdom of God.

00:12:18.176 --> 00:12:21.056
What's the kingdom of God? It's Jesus. He's the...

00:12:20.960 --> 00:12:25.120
As Origen said, the kingdom in person is not a sin.

00:12:24.864 --> 00:12:32.416
He's the coming together of divinity and humanity. He's what the new order looks like. And so we proclaim that.

00:12:32.256 --> 00:12:35.648
The kingdom has come and then we invite people to join

00:12:35.392 --> 00:12:39.904
into that kingdom. We're not just saying, "Be nice,

00:12:39.712 --> 00:12:43.968
I mean, boys and girls. I mean, be people with hearts of gold. Yeah.

00:12:43.552 --> 00:12:49.440
No, no, we're announcing this concrete breakthrough of divinity into our humanity.

00:12:49.536 --> 00:12:50.976
Proclaim.

00:12:50.880 --> 00:12:53.024
The kingdom of God.

00:12:52.992 --> 00:12:59.264
A new king has come around whom our lives need to be organized. Well, yeah.

00:12:59.136 --> 00:13:03.488
That remains the preaching and teaching of Job and the church.

00:13:03.424 --> 00:13:05.280
And then just one more.

00:13:06.656 --> 00:13:10.560
When the 72 came back, having received all this instruction,

00:13:10.784 --> 00:13:12.128
They say, "Lord,

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:15.648
Even the demons are subject to us because of your name.

00:13:16.128 --> 00:13:25.280
And then he says, Behold, I've given you power to tread upon serpents and scorpions, upon the full force of the enemy, and nothing will harm you.

00:13:26.048 --> 00:13:30.848
Wow cure the sick proclaim the kingdom and and the church

00:13:30.656 --> 00:13:32.512
Remember last week, the

00:13:32.352 --> 00:13:38.560
The gates of hell will not prevail against you. That means the gates of hell that we are going after are

00:13:38.592 --> 00:13:48.640
But we're not just enduring the onslaught from hell. We're going after the kingdom of the fallen powers. And we're going after their gates. That's the weakest part of

00:13:48.160 --> 00:13:58.208
part of the wall. That's what it means. The gates will not prevail against you. Do we have the courage and confidence as a church to face down the powers of darkness?

00:13:57.728 --> 00:14:03.392
Do we do it with our sacraments and the power of our word and the witness of our saints? Right. Right.

00:14:03.104 --> 00:14:13.152
Right. And when we're tempted to say, look, the world is dominated by wickedness and the devil has control over the world, he does not, not in the wake of the cross and resurrection.

00:14:12.672 --> 00:14:14.048
It's a resurrection.

00:14:13.760 --> 00:14:20.832
The church is meant to claim that power. Yes, even the demons are subject to us in your name. Amen.

00:14:20.928 --> 00:14:22.176
And so,

00:14:22.400 --> 00:14:24.576
Right to the present day

00:14:24.416 --> 00:14:28.032
The church goes forth with that kind of

00:14:28.224 --> 00:14:29.760
Confident power.

00:14:30.240 --> 00:14:34.272
Hey, everybody, spend a little time with this Luke chapter 10 passage, 2, 3, and 4.

00:14:34.272 --> 00:14:37.632
And it's telling us exactly who we are as a church today.

00:14:37.504 --> 00:14:39.648
And what our marching orders are.

00:14:39.712 --> 00:14:40.960
God bless you.

00:14:44.224 --> 00:14:48.416
Thank you for listening to this week's homily from Bishop Robert Barron.

00:14:48.192 --> 00:14:53.760
For more resources from Bishop Barron, please visit wordonfire.org.
